## Classification principles
- Classify based on the document itself, not on what someone might use it for later.
- Use document text as primary evidence.
- Use layout, stamps, tables, title blocks, signatures, and image/OCR cues as secondary evidence.
- Use filename and metadata only as supporting evidence.
- Never invent labels outside the allowed lists.

## NEN 2084 document_type
Choose exactly 1 value from this list:
- Overeenkomst
- Bestek
- Vergunning
- Beschikking
- Certificaat
- Technische tekening
- Berekening
- Programma van Eisen
- Schema
- 3D/BIM-model
- Rapport
- Inspectieresultaat
- Proces-verbaal
- Notulen
- Planning
- Begroting
- Handleiding
- Register
- Correspondentie
- Melding
- Foto/opname
- Norm
- Richtlijn
- Beleidsdocument

Rules for document_type:
- Document type is about the editorial form/function of the document, not the business process.
- Choose the most specific applicable type.
- If a PDF contains multiple subdocuments, classify the dominant/main document.
- Do not classify a substantive document as Correspondentie only because it has a cover letter or email wrapper.
- Prefer Inspectieresultaat over Rapport when the document is primarily an inspection outcome, checklist, or finding list.
- Prefer Schema over Technische tekening when the document is primarily a symbolic or logical representation instead of a scaled drawing.
- Prefer Vergunning for a permit as the main legal instrument; use Beschikking for another individual formal decision.

## GEBORA value_streams
Choose 1 to 3 values from this list, ordered from most relevant to least relevant:
- Strategisch en Tactisch Asset Management
- Investering en financiering
- Gebieds- en project (her-)ontwikkeling
- Bouwwerk realisatie
- Aan- en verkoop
- Exploitatie en commercieel beheer
- Gebruiks ondersteuning en functioneel beheer
- Technisch beheer en onderhoud
- Renovatie en vervanging
- Sloop en oogst
- Producten en materialen
- Personeel
- Materieel
- Logistiek en transport
- Kwaliteit, vergunning, toezicht, handhaving
- Registratie en administratie
- Hergebruik van circulaire producten

Rules for value_streams:
- Value streams describe the built-environment process context the document primarily supports.
- Be conservative: prefer 1 or 2 values; use 3 only when the document clearly spans multiple streams.
- Do not include adjacent or weakly related streams.
- Never return duplicates.
- Prefer streams that are explicitly evidenced by the document's purpose, issuer, audience, and content.

